Pre-Game Insights: Finland have won back-to-back games against the Republic of Ireland, both by a 1-0 scoreline in the 2020-21 Nations League.
Finland have struggled on the road, shipping at least two goals in each of their last five away games.
The Republic of Ireland have failed to score in 12 of their 18 Nations League matches to date, and have gone winless in all eight away games.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Finland's Teemu Pukki is the all-time top scorer for the team.
Fredrik Jensen could play a part for Finland, having scored the only goal in both wins over Ireland four years ago.
Others: The match could open up and end in a score draw, as both teams will sense this is one of their best chances to pick up three points.
